<br>
Came back at level 47 with a 46 ranger, and we were able to take most of the cave.  We couldn't clear it totally, but after about an hour, we did see ONE spell drop....and it was IVU.  I was happy, at least the trip wasn't a total loss.  And the ranger was able to find a drop for the shackles quest.  I felt sorry for my chanter friend, he came away with very little.  <br>
<br>
By the way, the xp for holmgresh seemed pretty bad.  Not to mention they can be pretty difficult for their level.  They would be a risky solo for me, at 47th level, and the cave definitely warrants a group.   <p>***  Givins, 46th level Erudite Wizard  ***</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubigboffer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bigboffer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/17/02 1:31:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> setting record straight</span><hr size=1> ok for all you desperate finger-wagglers out there that want this spell here is the low down...<br>
